sentences: Q-Tee (born Tatiana Mais, 1976 in Kidbrooke, London) is a British rapper.
At the time she recorded these songs she was 15 years old.
In 1990, she was the featured vocalist on History's UK No. 42 hit, "Afrika".
In 1993, Q-Tee provided rapping vocals on "Beautiful" by Babble, who were essentially the last two remaining members of Thompson Twins.
She also provided rapping vocals on Mark Morrison's 1996 single "Horny".
